value.value: A disorder characterized by abnormal sensual experience with the taste of foodstuffs; it can be related to a decrease in the sense of smell.
A disorder characterized by abnormally painful abdominal cramps during menses.
A disorder characterized by painful or difficult coitus.
A disorder characterized by an uncomfortable, often painful feeling in the stomach, resulting from impaired digestion. Symptoms include burning stomach, bloating, heartburn, nausea and vomiting.
A disorder characterized by impairment of verbal communication skills, often resulting from brain damage.

label.value: Ear and Labyrinth Disorders - Other, Specify, CTCAE

value.value: A disorder characterized by a sensation of marked discomfort in the ear.
A disorder characterized by swelling due to an excessive accumulation of fluid in the brain.
A disorder characterized by swelling due to excessive fluid accumulation in facial tissues.
A disorder characterized by swelling due to excessive fluid accumulation in the upper or lower extremities.
A disorder characterized by swelling due to excessive fluid accumulation in the trunk area.
A disorder characterized by problems related to ejaculation. This category includes premature, delayed, retrograde and painful ejaculation.
The percentage computed when the amount of blood ejected during a ventricular contraction of the heart is compared to the amount that was present prior to the contraction.

label.value: Electrocardiogram QT Corrected Interval Prolonged, CTCAE

value.value: A finding of a cardiac dysrhythmia characterized by an abnormally long corrected QT interval.
A disorder characterized by an infectious process involving the brain tissue.
A disorder characterized by an infectious process involving the brain and spinal cord tissues.

The Sloan-Kettering viruses (SKVs) are a group of transforming retroviruses that were isolated from chicken embryo cells which had been infected with the avian leukosis virus transformation-defective Bratislava 77 (tdB77). (from Li et al.  J Virol 1986;57:1065-72)
A disorder characterized by an infectious process involving the endocardial layer of the heart.
A disorder characterized by an infectious process involving the internal structures of the eye.
A disorder characterized by an infectious process involving the small and large intestines.
A disorder characterized by inflammation of the small and large intestines.
A disorder characterized by an abnormal communication between the urinary bladder and the intestine.
A disorder characterized by bleeding from the nose.
A disorder characterized by target lesions (a pink-red ring around a pale center).
A disorder characterized by generalized inflammatory erythema and exfoliation. The inflammatory process involves > 90% of the body surface area.
A finding of leakage due to breakdown of an esophageal anastomosis (surgical connection of two separate anatomic structures).
A disorder characterized by bleeding from the esophagus.
A disorder characterized by an infectious process involving the esophagus.
A disorder characterized by a necrotic process occurring in the esophageal wall.
A disorder characterized by blockage of the normal flow of the contents in the esophagus.
A disorder characterized by a sensation of marked discomfort in the esophageal region.
A disorder characterized by a rupture in the wall of the esophagus.
A disorder characterized by a narrowing of the lumen of the esophagus.
A single stranded RNA virus where the RNA strand is the complement of a mRNA.
A disorder characterized by a circumscribed, erosive lesion on the mucosal surface of the esophageal wall.
A disorder characterized by incomplete paralysis of an extraocular muscle.
A disorder characterized by abnormal, repetitive, involuntary muscle movements, frenzied speech and extreme restlessness.
A disorder characterized by an infectious process involving the eye.

A genus in the family retroviridae consisting of exogenous horizontally transmitted viruses found in mammals; associated with B or T cell leukemia/lymphoma with a long latency. Bovine Leukemia Virus is the type species. (from CRISP)
A disorder characterized by impaired eyelid function.
A disorder characterized by a reduction in the strength of the facial muscles.
A disorder characterized by dysfunction of the facial nerve (seventh cranial nerve).
A disorder characterized by a sensation of marked discomfort in the face.
A finding of sudden movement downward, usually resulting in injury.
A finding of leakage due to breakdown of a fallopian tube anastomosis (surgical connection of two separate anatomic structures).
